  {
    "user": "U06NSFX5119",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1742924914.365429",
    "edited": {
      "user": "U06NSFX5119",
      "ts": "1742924922.000000"
    },
    "client_msg_id": "a46efd13-9149-4ce4-afed-38f663f04be3",
    "text": "what would a baroque user interface look like?",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1742905419.328099",
    "parent_user_id": "U06SS0DHZD1",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "+OGzI",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "what would a baroque user interface look like?"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "present-company",
    "channel_id": "C01932BJGE8"
  },
  {
    "user": "U05PY5AQCA2",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1742925200.804279",
    "client_msg_id": "46D292E3-9065-4F38-A213-1222E4DF161C",
    "text": "I’ll need to experiment. I’m thinking subtle animation in the background, on borders and such. Maybe some more elaborate filigree? I’m planning on looking at video games for inspiration.\n\nAlso subtle background sounds. I think sound is greatly under-used in apps. If there were subtle background sounds indicating the state of an app, the user would come to learn them and be able to somewhat tell what an app was doing without looking.\n\nThe intent is to increase the delight in using the app, and to try to discover ways to improve usability. For example, I’ve a notion that you might use background animation behind the controls to indicate what just affected what when the user changes something.\n\nPartly vibes, at the moment, I admit.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1742905419.328099",
    "parent_user_id": "U06SS0DHZD1",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "qUP6E",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I’ll need to experiment. I’m thinking subtle animation in the background, on borders and such. Maybe some more elaborate filigree? I’m planning on looking at video games for inspiration.\n\nAlso subtle background sounds. I think sound is greatly under-used in apps. If there were subtle background sounds indicating the state of an app, the user would come to learn them and be able to somewhat tell what an app was doing without looking.\n\nThe intent is to increase the delight in using the app, and to try to discover ways to improve usability. For example, I’ve a notion that you might use background animation behind the controls to indicate what just affected what when the user changes something.\n\nPartly vibes, at the moment, I admit."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "present-company",
    "channel_id": "C01932BJGE8"
  },
